1
00:00:05,650 --> 00:00:09,049
 No... What did she do
so wrong that she has to apologize?

2
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:12,549
Because she didn't do what she was suppose to do, my
daughter just showed what was supposed to be done.

3
00:00:12,550 --> 00:00:16,879
What do you mean? Say something that makes sense.
Just because Bin is not doing well right now,

4
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:20,490
she expressed her frustration physically!

5
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:24,670
Bin's mother is no joke.

6
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:28,480
Ah, geez.

7
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:33,460
You... Apologize to Bin!

8
00:00:37,330 --> 00:00:41,530
If you don't, I won't send you home today.

9
00:00:42,570 --> 00:00:48,449
Who are you not let to my daughter go home?
Wow, you really have no conscience.

10
00:00:48,450 --> 00:00:52,319
Everyone knows that not one scene can
be shot because of her NGs (No Goods).

11
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,219
While filming, NGs are possible.

12
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:58,459
How are you going to make her into a child
actress without even understanding that?

13
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:00,909
Why don't you just do well yourself?

14
00:01:00,910 --> 00:01:05,799
Aigoo... What to do? She can't act. You should
have had her practice more before coming.

15
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,629
<i>If she has no talent, why
do you have her in acting?</i>

16
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:12,449
<i>This is her first shoot.</i> Her very first!

17
00:01:12,450 --> 00:01:15,590
Is there a kid who is good from start?

18
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:19,520
My mom is right.

19
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:31,750
You! Apologize to Bin right now!

20
00:01:32,730 --> 00:01:34,489
Won Shik! Won Shik!

21
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:36,450
Yes, Director?

22
00:01:39,380 --> 00:01:41,899
Let's rest for ten minutes.

23
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:46,960
Okay! We'll take a break!
A ten-minute break!

24
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:51,840
Let's go.

25
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:57,280
Excuse me.

26
00:01:58,890 --> 00:02:05,490
I'll have Bin practice her acting. Why don't have Ji Young
to apologize for pushing Bin earlier, however she wanted?

27
00:02:06,970 --> 00:02:10,180
Pushing me was wrong on your part.

28
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:14,800
Apologize.

29
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:21,510
Sorry. Sorry for pushing you earlier.

30
00:02:22,510 --> 00:02:24,610
Okay.

31
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:29,699
Enough? Let's go.

32
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,690
Mom is pitiful.

33
00:02:37,610 --> 00:02:39,129
You're not hurt?

34
00:02:39,130 --> 00:02:40,989
I'm not.

35
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:43,839
It's a break, let's practice.

36
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,670
Okay.

37
00:02:44,671 --> 00:02:46,920
You did so well at home, though.

38
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:56,829
But still, that's fascinating. How can
you fight during the first shooting?

39
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:59,699
She and her mom were terrible.

40
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:03,519
Let's say that she endured it for hundred times and
couldn't hold in the anger any longer so she pushed Bin.

41
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,749
Then the mom should scold her child, but
instead was talking all righteously.

42
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:09,409
That ahjumma is truly a strange ahjumma.

43
00:03:09,410 --> 00:03:12,599
That's right. When the
filming ended, I heard

44
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:16,699
that the kid was famous in her neighborhood and
that her Mother was known as a major crank.

45
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:21,419
She picked the wrong person. You're not
someone who would take that kind of behavior.

46
00:03:21,420 --> 00:03:25,450
Jye Yeong got a serious
scolding from Mom today.

47
00:03:37,110 --> 00:03:41,519
Bin, that today you called Mom, "Mom",

48
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:44,890
Mom was extremely happy.

49
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:52,369
Unni, you're now calling my Mom, "Mom"?

50
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:57,669
Then, I'll also call my
stepdad, "Dad." Daddy!

51
00:03:57,670 --> 00:04:00,580
Of course you can, our youngest daughter.

52
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:08,130
Ah, right. Bin, what about Mom?
Finish what you were saying.

53
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:16,449
Mom said to Jye Yeong that she wouldn't
let her go home until she apologized.

54
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:21,250
So, Jye Yeong said to me she was sorry.

55
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:25,469
Your Mom, since she was this little,

56
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:31,300
she never came home from
a fight she didn't win.

57
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:35,349
But, what if she torments Bin again?

58
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:38,459
That's why, for now, I need to
go to the filming location.

59
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:41,729
That way those people won't dare
bother Bin. Don't you think so, Bin?

60
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:46,949
Also, if I had gone with Grandpa it would have been a
disaster. He wouldn't have known how to do my hair, right?

61
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:51,609
True. Next time, I'll do your
hair and make-up even prettier.

62
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:55,699
Will you do my make-up
if I pass an audition?

63
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:58,129
Of course!

64
00:04:58,130 --> 00:05:02,179
If you get picked to be filmed,
I'll be really happy for you.

65
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:04,570
I would like that.

66
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:18,369
What's the matter? Are
you in pain somewhere?

67
00:05:18,370 --> 00:05:21,510
No. I'm fine.

68
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:26,479
What happened with Bin today, thank you.

69
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:33,789
You don't need to thank me. If there's any thanking to do, then I should
be saying it. When Woo Ri was crying about her dad, you were by her side.

70
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:37,509
And I'm grateful to you for always trying to
fulfill the dad role with Woo Ri and Woo Joo

71
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:40,529
That's given since I'm their dad now.

72
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:46,919
Still, is it easy to decide to do that from
the start? I'm in awe of you every day.

73
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,179
Why? I guess you're not doing
that with Soo and Bin, huh?

74
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:56,709
I'm not saying that I'm not. But honestly, I'm more careful
around them than I would be with Woo Young or Woo Ri.

75
00:05:56,710 --> 00:06:01,250
And at times, eyes from the
second floor are watching me too.

76
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:06,949
In any case, thank you for
opening up Bin's heart.

77
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:10,219
Soo and Bin don't even remember their mom.

78
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:16,229
Today, I was much happier
because Bin called me "Mom."

79
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:19,340
Thanks to you I got to hear
Woo Joo call me "Dad."

80
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:24,459
Daddy, read a book to me.

81
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:28,940
Ok, Woo Joo. What shall we read?
Let's read over here with me.

82
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:31,960
What should we read?

83
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:42,249
"Let's figure it out together."

84
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:45,579
"We can tell what it is just
by looking at the shape."

85
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:47,479
"It's time for school." It's written here.

86
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:50,549
"I will call it the lucky fin."

87
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:52,209
Call it a lucky fin.

88
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:56,210
"It will bring you luck."

89
00:07:01,150 --> 00:07:05,489
- Wait a minute. Bellflower root. There is Bellflower root in the fridge.
- Okay.

90
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,610
Get that out too.

91
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:13,730
Let's see if the fish is done grilling.

92
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:25,889
What's going on? What's with the
sumptuous feast for breakfast?

93
00:07:25,890 --> 00:07:29,589
I'm trying to feed Teacher Kim.

94
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:34,569
Teacher Kim? Tae Min? Why would
Tae Min be eating at our house?

95
00:07:34,570 --> 00:07:38,449
You said that Teacher Kim is
not eating at his home lately.

96
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:42,269
If he is not being fed at his house, then we
should at least feed him before sending him home.

97
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:45,560
They said they're coming; I
wonder why they're not here yet.

98
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:53,409
I might not know how Teacher
Kim's mom treats you, but

99
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:55,679
take a look at Teacher Kim.

100
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,769
Look at how hard he is trying even
though we are objecting to him.

101
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:02,399
He says he'll handle everything
to change his mother's mind.

102
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:06,709
He even comes here in the
morning to run with your dad.

103
00:08:06,710 --> 00:08:09,819
I also tried to behave well.

104
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:13,550
Calling her "ahjumma" is behaving well?

105
00:08:14,650 --> 00:08:19,749
If you showed your temper once that's
enough. Also, you still like Teacher Kim.

106
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:24,850
Then you should also lower your head and get
in there if you're not planning to break-up.

107
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:34,690
Let's see.

108
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:40,259
I have octopus that I bought. Should I
cook it quickly in the pressure cooker?

109
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:44,230
Madam, there's no space on the table.

110
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,609
Really? Bin really said "Mother"?

111
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:05,789
Yes. So our whole family
were all surprised. Right?

112
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:08,339
Yeah. That's right. I was
really surprised, too.

113
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:12,369
Woo Joo called me "Dad" too,
after hearing Bin say it.

114
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:16,509
That's great, I'm glad. It boosted the
kid's confidence and gave affection too.

115
00:09:16,510 --> 00:09:20,070
I'm glad that the kids' mom
went there instead of me!

116
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:23,019
Then I'll be on my way.

117
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,829
You're not thirsty today?

118
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:26,599
Why don't you eat with us before you go?

119
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,489
Where? On the third floor?

120
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:32,619
Mother-in-law asked me to make sure
he eats with us before he goes.

121
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:35,969
Really? Can I really do that?

122
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:40,329
Well, I didn't allow it yet.
My principles are unchanged.

123
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:45,149
I can only allow it after you convince
your parents. Before then, there's no way.

124
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:47,689
He's trying his best to convince
them right now, Father.

125
00:09:47,690 --> 00:09:51,209
Don't be like that and
please open up your heart.

126
00:09:51,210 --> 00:09:56,050
It's hard enough for them. It'll
be nice to lessen their burden.

127
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:00,419
Come on, let's go in. Come
on kids, let's go in.

128
00:10:00,420 --> 00:10:01,859
Yes. Let's go, Teacher.

129
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:03,519
Let's go. Hurry up.

130
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,230
Let's go.

131
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:15,669
I don't want to eat breakfast, Grandma.

132
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:21,029
How can you go to work on an empty stomach?
Just have a little at least.

133
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:23,849
It's okay. My stomach doesn't
feel good, that's why.

134
00:10:23,850 --> 00:10:25,849
You still don't feel okay?

135
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:29,069
Then... You should go to the hospital.

136
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:35,619
I was going to, but I'm too busy with
work because there's an event going on.

137
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:37,489
I'll go once it's over.

138
00:10:37,490 --> 00:10:38,939
<i>- Go and wash up.
- Yes.</i>

139
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:41,199
The kids must be back.

140
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,510
<i>Make sure to wash well.</i>

141
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:58,189
Teacher Kim, please eat.

142
00:10:58,190 --> 00:11:01,249
Yes. I will eat well, Mother.

143
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:03,449
Okay.

144
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:07,660
But... Where's Jin Joo?

145
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:16,119
Let her be. I think she doesn't know
what to do after asking to break up.

146
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:21,589
You prepared so much food. She's usually
really good to her sons-in-law.

147
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:25,979
Teacher Kim, don't think
about anything and eat up.

148
00:11:25,980 --> 00:11:27,520
Yes.

149
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,370
Oh, yes.

150
00:11:34,650 --> 00:11:37,049
Side dishes are really delicious, Mother.

151
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:38,259
Really?

152
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:41,029
I'm relieved the taste is to your liking.

153
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:43,380
- Eat this as well.
- Yes.

154
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:47,529
- What would you like, Honey?
- Me?

155
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:51,179
Why are you making a face?
Hurry up and eat.

156
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:53,230
I am eating.

157
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,149
I want to see Tae Min, too.

158
00:12:16,150 --> 00:12:20,110
I want to have breakfast with Tae Min, too!

159
00:12:25,090 --> 00:12:30,919
Then we'll do a separate photo session with Kim Sang Min
instead of sending out reporters to his One Point lesson.

160
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:34,129
VIPs are sensitive to being photographed,
so let's pay special attention to that.

161
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:36,619
Myung Jae, please redo the
time table and upload it.

162
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:38,159
Yes, I will.

163
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,639
Then our meeting for today is over.

164
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:44,289
By the way, Manager Do stopped
by the business management team.

165
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:45,719
I had a short conversation with him,

166
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:50,719
and he said that Kim Sang Min's parents
were on the One Point lesson guest list.

167
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,139
Really?

168
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:54,099
Did you check the guest list?

169
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:58,309
Yes, I did. Manager Do told
me not to mind it too much.

170
00:12:58,310 --> 00:13:01,049
He said he only mentioned it so that it doesn't
come as a surprise on the day of the event.

171
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:03,989
How did we not know about it
when they're our brand's VIPs?

172
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:07,369
There are a lot of people who don't take
part in events even if they're VIPs.

173
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:10,489
On top of that, Kim Sang Min doesn't
really go around with his parents.

174
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:15,370
That's true. The agency has always followed him
around instead, since the beginning of his career.

175
00:13:25,970 --> 00:13:28,249
What do we do during the One Point lesson?

176
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:31,149
Shouldn't we take the 2nd floor
adults off of the guest list?

177
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:33,549
We already made calls and
sent out the invites.

178
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:37,119
It's one thing if they said they're not coming,
but we can't prevent them from attending.

179
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:40,320
What if they fight again that day?

180
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,060
Come in.

181
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:54,479
Where are your parents?

182
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:57,949
Oh, they went down to Ganghwado in
the morning for something urgent.

183
00:13:57,950 --> 00:14:02,009
Come over here. Sit here. I'll be
back after putting the cake away.

184
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,530
Okay.

185
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:16,389
It was hot coming over here, right? Why did you insist
on coming by yourself when I offered to pick you up?

186
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:18,199
Why should you bother yourself?

187
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:23,010
It was nice to look around the apartment
complex after getting off the bus.

188
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:31,050
When I came over last time for dinner, I didn't get a
chance to look around, but the house is very clean.

189
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:37,399
Where's your room? Mom told me to
look and see if you need anything.

190
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:41,609
I don't need anything. Over there is my
room, and over there is Tae Min's room.

191
00:14:41,610 --> 00:14:45,589
When we get married and Tae Min moves
out, I'll make his room into your study.

192
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:47,189
Really?

193
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:51,559
Then, what we need first
is a desk and a bookcase.

194
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:54,610
I'll get those things ready myself, too.

195
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:03,810
How can I just move in empty-handed?
I should buy things we need.

196
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:07,490
I told you, I'll get everything ready.

197
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:20,409
Sang Min, what is all this?

198
00:15:20,410 --> 00:15:24,089
Isn't it nice that there are many of me?

199
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:28,729
Once we get married, let's keep one
here and keep one in your study.

200
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:30,909
When I'm traveling for competitions,
you'll be scared being home by yourself.

201
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:34,689
Won't it be reassuring? Look at me as
much as you want whenever you miss me.

202
00:15:34,690 --> 00:15:37,360
I'll think about it...

203
00:15:50,170 --> 00:15:53,379
We should get a new bed.

204
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:58,130
Yeon Tae. Sit down over here.

205
00:15:59,090 --> 00:16:01,219
Why?

206
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:03,520
Sit over here.

207
00:16:15,970 --> 00:16:20,190
Since you're in my room like
this, it finally feels real.

208
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:24,859
The fact that we're getting married
and becoming husband and wife.

209
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:29,829
After we get married, this room
will become our newlywed room.

210
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,789
Right.

211
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:37,099
Let's live really happily and well.
I will make you very happy.

212
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,679
I will make you very happy, too.

213
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:44,210
Just having you next to
me is happiness for me.

214
00:16:56,850 --> 00:17:01,839
Yeon Doo. Yeon Doo, what's the matter?

215
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:05,799
I think we should keep the
life-size photos out of our home.

216
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:07,529
Why?

217
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:10,360
I like the real thing.

218
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,159
Huh? That...

219
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:16,250
Why not finish what we started...

220
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:27,289
I was going to buy some dishes, but you live better
than I expected for two men sharing a house together.

221
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:30,759
Since I have to watch what I eat, I try
to eat at home as much as possible.

222
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:35,429
Tae Min was the one in charge of cooking, but I've
been working really hard to learn how to cook.

223
00:17:35,430 --> 00:17:38,319
You saw last time, right? My lunchbox.

224
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:41,719
Then when we get married,
you're going to cook for me?

225
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:45,710
Of course! Come and sit. It's all done.

226
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:55,120
I will eat well.

227
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:02,320
Ouch!

228
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:06,869
That's why you should watch it.

229
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:10,920
You were cute, so I tried
to do a cream-kiss...

230
00:18:12,020 --> 00:18:13,850
Ouch, it hurts.

231
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:18,250
What about the trip? Have
you thought about it?

232
00:18:20,430 --> 00:18:24,290
Don't be like that and let's go. Even
if it's somewhere close by, huh?

233
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:31,619
To be honest, I wanted to go see the
ocean before the summer was over, but...

234
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:37,049
Really?! Then how about Gangneung?
Have you been to Gangneung?

235
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,909
Go on a two day and one night trip?

236
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:41,029
Yeah. I have another morning off.

237
00:18:41,030 --> 00:18:47,320
Since the shoot is in the afternoon the next day, I can take
my time coming back in the morning. Let's go, Soon Young.

238
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:54,559
But still, is it okay that we go off on a trip by ourselves
when your parents are working at the restaurant?

239
00:18:54,560 --> 00:19:00,149
Of course it's okay. You know my parents aren't the
type to make us self-conscious about those things.

240
00:19:00,150 --> 00:19:05,759
Also, you will soon start to show, so it'll
be harder for you to move around as easily.

241
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:09,810
While I have the time, let's
go on a short trip, huh?

242
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:15,420
Hello.

243
00:19:15,421 --> 00:19:16,919
Yes, where are you off to?

244
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,539
I'm going to Father-in-law's restaurant
to take back the kimchi container.

245
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:23,089
Ah, I was on my way to the in-law's too.
That's great. Let's go together.

246
00:19:23,090 --> 00:19:24,109
Okay.

247
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:26,489
Let's go.

248
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:29,030
<i>Please come this way.</i>

249
00:19:30,290 --> 00:19:35,739
What brings you by at this hour? We
were about to close and leave soon.

250
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:39,269
And you too. You could have brought
this back another time, too.

251
00:19:39,270 --> 00:19:41,739
Why would you bother bringing
it back so late in the evening?

252
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:45,139
I had indigestion, so I
walked here as exercise.

253
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:48,219
By chance I met her by the stairs.

254
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:53,719
And she said she was coming
by here so I came along.

255
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,389
I'm glad you did.

256
00:19:55,390 --> 00:20:02,789
But, are the wedding preparations going well
for your daughter? Do you have a date set?

257
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:05,079
We're thinking about a fall wedding.

258
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,990
Omo! You found a wedding venue?

259
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:12,029
Well...

260
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:16,419
Oh don't worry. She's
marrying someone nice,

261
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:19,049
so why would you bother to think about me?

262
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:23,090
Jin Joo is Jin Joo, and your
daughter should get married.

263
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:32,259
But, I don't think it'll be easy on
Jin Joo to go through a breakup.

264
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:36,890
Apparently, Teacher Kim comes
over every morning for exercise.

265
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:41,749
Son-in-law and the kids
exercise every morning.

266
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:46,179
And he comes over all the way from
his house to here every morning.

267
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:49,979
Today he ate breakfast with
us before he went home!

268
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,139
I see.

269
00:20:52,140 --> 00:21:00,140
In-law, you're okay with Jin Joo and Yeon
Tae marrying into the same family, right?

270
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:07,659
<i>Of course she doesn't like it.
I don't like it either.</i>

271
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:12,130
<i>Our Jin Joo will get compared to
Yeon Tae for the rest of her life.</i>

272
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:17,289
Tell me. You don't mind, right?

273
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:20,769
Well, what is there for me to mind?

274
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:23,919
It's just that... you should first...

275
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,929
Right? You're happy too, right?

276
00:21:26,930 --> 00:21:30,219
Becoming sisters-in-law as friends will bring them
together for family events and family get-togethers.

277
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:34,299
I think it'll be fun for them.
Don't you think so?

278
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:37,670
I heard the brothers get
along really well, too.

279
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:43,059
Yeon Tae will become Jin Joo's hyungnim.
Is that okay with you?

280
00:21:43,060 --> 00:21:45,959
Who cares about those titles these days?
I heard that young people nowadays

281
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:49,919
just call each other by their names
as equals. Isn't that right?

282
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:54,810
Well, that's true. You can always
change those titles later on.

283
00:21:56,150 --> 00:22:02,889
In-law, I'm determined to get
Teacher Kim and Jin Joo married.

284
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:05,369
How?

285
00:22:05,370 --> 00:22:11,999
You should pretend you don't know anything. It
could make it awkward for you with your in-laws.

286
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:18,689
I mean, how will you get them
married when they're so against it?

287
00:22:18,690 --> 00:22:21,039
I will have to think of
ways from this moment on.

288
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:23,729
They say that even if the sky
falls, there's a way out.

289
00:22:23,730 --> 00:22:27,630
I'm sure there will be a way
if I use any and all methods.

290
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,629
<i>Is she...</i>

291
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:41,429
<i>Right? I think she's pregnant!</i>

292
00:22:41,430 --> 00:22:43,529
Why? You have indigestion?

293
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:47,079
Yes. I've been like this
since a while back.

294
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:49,929
Really? Since when?

295
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:52,170
It's been a little while.

296
00:22:54,420 --> 00:22:58,629
<i>Maybe she's pregnant with her sixth?</i>

297
00:22:58,630 --> 00:23:00,880
<i>I know, right?</i>

298
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:09,439
<i>Then they'll have six kids... I
just can't be happy about it...</i>

299
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:12,689
<i>Well, who cares? There's
us on the 2nd floor.</i>

300
00:23:12,690 --> 00:23:15,159
Don't worry. If you have a
baby, I'll raise the baby.

301
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,409
Pardon?

302
00:23:17,410 --> 00:23:20,549
Oh... Are you pregnant?

303
00:23:20,550 --> 00:23:25,070
No, Mother. Oh, no. It's not like that.

304
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,589
Really? Are you sure?

305
00:23:28,590 --> 00:23:31,080
Yes. I'm not, Mother.

306
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,549
<i>Is it possible you're pregnant
with your third child?</i>

307
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:44,009
<i>It's not like that.</i>

308
00:23:44,010 --> 00:23:50,469
<i>I've had indigestion and felt
uncomfortable since a little while back.</i>

309
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:53,410
<i>It's not a baby, Mom.</i>

310
00:23:55,640 --> 00:24:00,449
I've had a bit of indigestion and felt
uncomfortable since a little while back.

311
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:05,749
I think it's because I've had a lot of things
on my mind these days with work and our kids.

312
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:08,199
- Are you taking medicine?
- I should.

313
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:13,919
You should make sure to take medicine.
There's no use in ignoring pain away.

314
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:17,989
Oh, I thought you were
pregnant and was so surprised!

315
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:21,659
I thought you might be going
from having five kids to six!

316
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:27,420
But then again, it wouldn't be hard to raise
six when you're already raising five.

317
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,999
You don't understand me, right?

318
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:41,029
You think I'm bothering my in-laws
with their wedding preparations.

319
00:24:41,030 --> 00:24:42,899
It's about your child.

320
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:45,789
How can I not understand
when I'm a mom, too?

321
00:24:45,790 --> 00:24:50,529
Oh, it's something to congratulate of course
when her daughter is loved and getting married.

322
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:53,569
But I worry about Jin Joo.

323
00:24:53,570 --> 00:24:59,319
Aiyoo... I'm wondering what I was doing
while she was suffering so much.

324
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:02,679
You were taking care of Soo and Bin well.

325
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,959
I hope my in-laws will do
well with the wedding.

326
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:13,289
And, when Jin Joo has a good man,
I'd like to marry her off fast.

327
00:25:13,290 --> 00:25:18,049
By the way, Woo Young's mom...

328
00:25:18,050 --> 00:25:23,499
You were nauseous earlier...

329
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:26,649
I really am not pregnant!

330
00:25:26,650 --> 00:25:29,409
How long have you been that way?

331
00:25:29,410 --> 00:25:33,170
It's no big deal. I used to get like
that when I was under a little stress.

332
00:25:34,390 --> 00:25:40,269
By the way, you're coming to our company
tomorrow for One Point lesson, right?

333
00:25:40,270 --> 00:25:45,969
Ah... Because of Jin Joo, I don't even know if I want
to go see Kim Sang Min. I don't know if I'll go or not.

334
00:25:45,970 --> 00:25:50,040
They said Kim Sang Min's
parents will be there also.

335
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:53,459
They will be there?

336
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:57,530
Yes, I'm giving you a heads up.

337
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:19,299
Why are you standing here?
Let's go in, huh?

338
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:21,039
Mom.

339
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:23,299
What?

340
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:26,190
I really hate being in Seoul.

341
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:33,589
I want to go down to Kyung
Joo, to Aunt's house.

342
00:26:33,590 --> 00:26:35,919
To Kyung Joo?

343
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:42,139
I want to go to Aunt's pension
and help a little with chores.

344
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:47,650
I want to escape from here and
live in a new environment, Mom.

345
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:55,630
I want to go down there and
forget about everything.

346
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:11,779
Where is So Young?

347
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:16,350
She was frustrated so she'll go home
early, after getting some fresh air.

348
00:27:17,710 --> 00:27:24,579
Why don't you leave the shop to me and
go down to Kyung Joo with So Young?

349
00:27:24,580 --> 00:27:26,319
Kyung Joo?

350
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:33,550
So Young wants to go down to her aunt's in Kyung
Joo because she really hates being in Seoul.

351
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:44,989
She's really not living. Her
mind is somewhere else.

352
00:27:44,990 --> 00:27:47,660
She's like a shell, moving around.

353
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:50,859
I'm sorry.

354
00:27:50,860 --> 00:27:54,239
I'm not saying it to hear that from you.

355
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:57,369
So Young is not in her
right mind, right now.

356
00:27:57,370 --> 00:28:04,210
I'm afraid to send her down all by herself, so
please go with her and take a good care of her.

357
00:28:06,940 --> 00:28:11,650
What's the matter? You don't want
to do it because of your kids?

358
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:16,830
Because I just started meeting Woo Ri...

359
00:28:19,220 --> 00:28:24,459
No. Since So Young became like
this, how can I say anything?

360
00:28:24,460 --> 00:28:27,960
I'll try to discuss itwith So Young.

361
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:33,289
When your spouse is having a hard
time, you should be by her side.

362
00:28:33,290 --> 00:28:39,489
I knew nothing good would come out of
this kind of marriage, but I let you

363
00:28:39,490 --> 00:28:42,379
because So Young said she
couldn't live without you.

364
00:28:42,380 --> 00:28:49,010
You became a couple after all that.
You can't end it like this, right?

365
00:28:53,580 --> 00:29:00,250
Go down there with So Young.
I'll call my younger sister.

366
00:29:07,390 --> 00:29:10,470
Did they go to work already?

367
00:29:13,630 --> 00:29:16,299
Son-in-law Lee! Son-in-law Lee!

368
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:21,169
Talk to me a bit before you go.
I just need five minutes.

369
00:29:21,170 --> 00:29:24,140
- I'll wait in the car.
- Okay.

370
00:29:26,050 --> 00:29:29,629
You know we'll have the One Point lesson today,
don't you? Did you get an invitation card?

371
00:29:29,630 --> 00:29:32,890
Oh... Yes, I got it.

372
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:37,689
Do you know that your wife is ill?

373
00:29:37,690 --> 00:29:39,049
Pardon?

374
00:29:39,050 --> 00:29:43,679
When we were at the restaurant
yesterday, she was having dry heaves!

375
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:48,010
She's not pregnant, but her stomach
doesn't feel good and has indigestion.

376
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:55,119
Look, you must take her to the hospital. You can't
leave her like this, and let the disease progress.

377
00:29:55,120 --> 00:30:00,930
If something doesn't feel right, even a tiny bit, you
have to take her to the hospital fast! Got that?

378
00:30:02,430 --> 00:30:07,079
Yes... Mother-in-law.
Thanks for your advice.

379
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,150
<i>Get going. Go.</i>

380
00:30:26,690 --> 00:30:29,779
She wasn't pregnant, and
yet she was nauseous?

381
00:30:29,780 --> 00:30:35,209
Yes, I didn't sleep at all last night.

382
00:30:35,210 --> 00:30:39,219
I couldn't bring myself to tell
Son-in-law Lee about that.

383
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:44,600
When I saw the kids' mom like
that, I thought of Jin Young.

384
00:30:45,470 --> 00:30:48,579
Aigoo, this is so worrisome.

385
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:53,079
Our Jin Young went to the hospital like
that and got diagnosed with stomach cancer.

386
00:30:53,080 --> 00:30:55,339
<i>Don't talk like that!</i>

387
00:30:55,340 --> 00:30:58,540
It's only morning and you're
already making me nervous!

388
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:08,179
Aren't we going to get going?

389
00:31:08,180 --> 00:31:11,470
Are you... sick?

390
00:31:12,250 --> 00:31:14,769
Me? Where?

391
00:31:14,770 --> 00:31:20,169
They said yesterday... that you
threw up at the restaurant.

392
00:31:20,170 --> 00:31:23,979
They also said that you had heartburn
and you couldn't digest your food well.

393
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:29,989
Oh, that. When I get stressed and
tired, I get stomach distress...

394
00:31:29,990 --> 00:31:35,850
Why... didn't you tell me about that?

395
00:31:37,940 --> 00:31:40,339
Why didn't you tell me?!

396
00:31:40,340 --> 00:31:44,769
If you are sick, you should say so. I
should be the very first one you tell!

397
00:31:44,770 --> 00:31:48,829
It hasn't been that long.
It was a little ache and...

398
00:31:48,830 --> 00:31:51,830
What do you mean, "It wasn't that bad"?
Are you a doctor?

399
00:31:53,090 --> 00:31:58,800
Why are you angry? If I got any worse, I
was just going to go to the hospital.

400
00:31:59,950 --> 00:32:03,199
<i>My wife had stomach cancer.</i>

401
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:09,489
<i>We had two thirds of her stomach cut
out and we thought she could live,</i>

402
00:32:09,490 --> 00:32:15,000
<i>since we said, "Let's overcome
this and have another kid."</i>

403
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:22,560
<i>And that's how she died.</i>

404
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:34,089
No way. It's not that at all.

405
00:32:34,090 --> 00:32:38,810
How can you know that? Like I
asked before, are you a doctor?

406
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:57,209
Really? They said they would
let Jin Joo get married too?

407
00:32:57,210 --> 00:33:01,449
But I hear that the potential
In-Laws are against the marriage.

408
00:33:01,450 --> 00:33:06,329
They said they would find a way. I
don't understand what they mean.

409
00:33:06,330 --> 00:33:11,299
Doesn't that mean they would just forget about the means and
ways and just force her to get married? Aren't I right, honey?

410
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:16,220
Jin Joo getting married
will make us feel better.

411
00:33:17,710 --> 00:33:19,999
I, too, really want things
to go well for Jin Joo.

412
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:26,120
But you know, we'll all be intertwined. Once she gets
married, things won't always be so quiet anymore.

413
00:33:27,650 --> 00:33:30,899
Um... Mother and Father...

414
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,550
Yes?

415
00:33:33,550 --> 00:33:35,649
I have something I need to tell you...

416
00:33:35,650 --> 00:33:37,159
What is it? Tell me.

417
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:42,959
Is it okay if we go somewhere nearby for
a trip? Just for one night and two days.

418
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:48,939
Go ahead since the weather is hot.
Get some fresh breezes.

419
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:54,229
Of course! But why are you talking so carefully?
You worried we would catch on to something?

420
00:33:54,230 --> 00:33:58,339
No, no. It's not that.
But anyway, thank you!

421
00:33:58,340 --> 00:33:59,769
Where are going to go?

422
00:33:59,770 --> 00:34:02,419
Somewhere in Gyeongpodae. Gangneung.

423
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:05,129
Gangneung is great, of course!

424
00:34:05,130 --> 00:34:08,859
You are pregnant so go
and come back carefully.

425
00:34:08,860 --> 00:34:10,920
Yes, Father!

426
00:34:13,220 --> 00:34:15,669
Um... Mom...?

427
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:17,589
What is it?

428
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:22,629
I have to... go out for training too.

429
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:23,789
What kind of training?

430
00:34:23,790 --> 00:34:30,489
Oh, Oh... A kind of support training.

431
00:34:30,490 --> 00:34:31,210
Huh?

432
00:34:31,211 --> 00:34:35,579
You should go then if it has to do with
school work. How long will it take?

433
00:34:35,580 --> 00:34:38,179
One... One night and two days.

434
00:34:38,180 --> 00:34:41,889
Then, you should prepare.
Did you pack things?

435
00:34:41,890 --> 00:34:43,550
Yes, I did...

436
00:34:46,510 --> 00:34:51,139
What? The second Hyungim couple
are going on a trip to Ganeung?

437
00:34:51,140 --> 00:34:54,970
I think we should go somewhere
else, other than Ganeung.

438
00:34:55,830 --> 00:34:58,549
We have to go to Ganeung though.
Where should we go?

439
00:34:58,550 --> 00:35:03,899
The new Unni talked about Gyeougpo dae. There's a
hundred-percent chance that we'll run into each other.

440
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:08,869
I even lied to them saying that I have to
go on some training. I can't be caught.

441
00:35:08,870 --> 00:35:13,139
Of course we can't be caught. I
even lied about going on training.

442
00:35:13,140 --> 00:35:16,239
Then, then, then...

443
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:20,519
Then, how about Ganghwado? Since it's
not too far and I know the area.

444
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:24,509
Also, it's totally opposite
direction from Ganeung as well.

445
00:35:24,510 --> 00:35:29,650
I like it. Then, let's go to Ganghwado this
time and let's go to Ganeung next time.

446
00:35:30,500 --> 00:35:32,850
Well, that's that!

447
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:37,099
Why are you trying to
buy this type of thing?

448
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:42,529
What can we not do for our child? Teacher Kim
even bought flowers when he came to our house.

449
00:35:42,530 --> 00:35:44,449
Is that the same thing?

450
00:35:44,450 --> 00:35:46,109
I don't know. I don't know.

451
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:48,819
I'm just going to give what I give
and you just worry about the price.

452
00:35:48,820 --> 00:35:51,310
Wait a minute... This...

453
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:53,659
Are you going to eat that, ma'am?

454
00:35:53,660 --> 00:35:57,029
I'm going to give this to someone important
