about it before I started.

692
00:53:33,330 --> 00:53:34,759
I'll take care of it.
Hurry up and bring it.

693
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:38,729
No, go eat dinner. It's all done

694
00:53:38,730 --> 00:53:40,709
- Hurry up. Let's do it after dinner.
- Let's eat dinner.

695
00:53:40,710 --> 00:53:42,089
Let's eat, let's eat.

696
00:53:42,090 --> 00:53:43,960
Woo Joo, come here.

697
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:03,460
We have arrived, my dear.

698
00:54:09,340 --> 00:54:12,659
It's a triplex so I was worried about finding a
vacant room but I lucked out in getting a room.

699
00:54:12,660 --> 00:54:16,229
Just as if this place was
ready for us all along.

700
00:54:16,230 --> 00:54:18,220
I'm so excited.

701
00:54:23,080 --> 00:54:27,229
Yeon Doo, what's wrong?

702
00:54:27,230 --> 00:54:28,939
This car!

703
00:54:28,940 --> 00:54:30,769
What's wrong? You're scaring me!

704
00:54:30,770 --> 00:54:32,679
Yeon Tae?

705
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:34,319
What the heck?

706
00:54:34,320 --> 00:54:36,710
You bastard!

707
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:40,220
Lee Yeon Tae!

708
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:48,410
Hyungnim! What are you doing here?

709
00:54:49,250 --> 00:54:53,129
I knew it. I knew something was fishy.

710
00:54:53,130 --> 00:54:56,480
Hey, Lee Yeon Tae, is this
a training institute?

711
00:54:57,610 --> 00:54:59,349
What happened was...

712
00:54:59,350 --> 00:55:02,279
Hyungnim, Yeon Tae did nothing wrong. I...

713
00:55:02,280 --> 00:55:03,930
Shut up!

714
00:55:04,780 --> 00:55:06,730
Oh my goodness.

715
00:55:07,940 --> 00:55:14,469
What's so wrong about taking a trip with my girlfriend
that I'm going to be married to soon, Hyungmin?

716
00:55:14,470 --> 00:55:16,250
That's right!

717
00:55:17,250 --> 00:55:21,419
Of course, it's not wrong if I don't find out
about it. But I found out about it though.

718
00:55:21,420 --> 00:55:24,599
That's where it went wrong, you punk!

719
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:30,699
But are you proud of
what you did, Hyungnim?

720
00:55:30,700 --> 00:55:33,890
You also did something, even
before you got married.

721
00:55:36,180 --> 00:55:38,839
Anyhow, your sister here

722
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:43,319
shouldn't be repressed because I feel
that it's wrong for you to do that.

723
00:55:43,320 --> 00:55:45,039
Go and ask anybody in the streets,

724
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:47,659
if they meet their little
sister at a motel like this,

725
00:55:47,660 --> 00:55:50,709
how the big brother must feel.

726
00:55:50,710 --> 00:55:52,660
It would suck.

727
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:58,299
Stop it, Honey. They are here
to have a good time, you know.

728
00:55:58,300 --> 00:56:03,089
Why don't we just go grill some
meat together since we're all here.

729
00:56:03,090 --> 00:56:06,799
Miss, you haven't had
anything to eat yet right?

730
00:56:06,800 --> 00:56:09,899
Yes, that would be nice.
What do you think, Sang Min?

731
00:56:09,900 --> 00:56:13,530
If it's okay with Hyungnim.

732
00:56:14,350 --> 00:56:17,099
Alright then. Why don't we
go and drop off our stuff?

733
00:56:17,100 --> 00:56:19,890
Yes, I understand, Hyungnim.

734
00:56:21,270 --> 00:56:24,399
Where are you going right now?

735
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:26,319
What? Our room is this way.

736
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:28,069
Oh, really?

737
00:56:28,070 --> 00:56:33,870
Then, you sleep with me. And Yeon
Tae can sleep with Soon Young.

738
00:56:45,320 --> 00:56:49,909
Doesn't this feel like we are on a college
field trip? Isn't this quite nice?

739
00:56:49,910 --> 00:56:56,579
Yes sir. If I had known this was going to happen, I could've invited Yeon Tae's
big brother and his family so this could be more like a family outing, right?

740
00:56:56,580 --> 00:57:00,039
Why are you playing along, buddy?

741
00:57:00,040 --> 00:57:02,699
Hyungnim.

742
00:57:02,700 --> 00:57:06,799
Don't worry about my parents.
I won't tell them anything.

743
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:09,969
I am a guy who's good at keeping secrets.

744
00:57:09,970 --> 00:57:13,799
Yes, I'm really grateful.

745
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:19,829
By the way, you don't snore when you sleep,
right? Because I'm a sensitive sleeper.

746
00:57:19,830 --> 00:57:23,359
I sleep like a dead mouse (really
quietly), so don't worry.

747
00:57:23,360 --> 00:57:26,299
I could really just die because
I'm so freaking upset you know.

748
00:57:26,300 --> 00:57:28,379
Ah, it's so hot.

749
00:57:28,380 --> 00:57:31,069
You're so funny.

750
00:57:31,070 --> 00:57:33,070
I don't know.

751
00:57:36,380 --> 00:57:40,859
We suddenly changed our destination,
so I wonder how we met like this.

752
00:57:40,860 --> 00:57:45,679
We barely made reservations
for this inn, you know.

753
00:57:45,680 --> 00:57:47,470
Yes.

754
00:57:49,750 --> 00:57:52,269
My husband can be a bit particular, right?

755
00:57:52,270 --> 00:57:56,459
You could have at least told me
about it before you came here.

756
00:57:56,460 --> 00:58:00,439
I know, right? Oh, that's not true!

757
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:04,879
I think that it's meaningful that I'm
able to be here with you like this.

758
00:58:04,880 --> 00:58:06,279
I bet that's not true.

759
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:08,720
Really.

760
00:58:11,490 --> 00:58:14,959
Here we are. Yeon Tae, you should
eat to your heart's content.

761
00:58:14,960 --> 00:58:18,330
Okay, I'm going to eat <i>a lot</i>.

762
00:58:19,210 --> 00:58:22,290
Brother-in-law, come here and eat!

763
00:58:23,410 --> 00:58:27,730
- Soon Young, this is the perfect timing, so you should eat now. Okay?
- Alright, Honey.

764
00:58:31,830 --> 00:58:33,500
Eat.

765
00:58:37,040 --> 00:58:39,340
Yes, I'm coming.

766
00:58:59,010 --> 00:59:01,410
<i>Yeon Doo, are you sleeping?</i>

767
00:59:19,330 --> 00:59:20,930
Ah.

768
00:59:22,250 --> 00:59:25,419
You didn't wake up because of me, right?

769
00:59:25,420 --> 00:59:27,289
I couldn't sleep.

770
00:59:27,290 --> 00:59:29,079
You didn't wake up because
your brother scared you?

771
00:59:29,080 --> 00:59:33,319
No. What will you do if you can't sleep?

772
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:39,549
Starting from early morning you drove us here and then you grilled the meat. And I'm
sure you're tired because you did all that. Is my second brother sleeping well?

773
00:59:39,550 --> 00:59:44,190
He said that he is a very light sleeper but
he started to snore the moment he laid down.

774
00:59:45,360 --> 00:59:48,939
I feel sorry towards my
brother and his wife.

775
00:59:48,940 --> 00:59:52,989
They came here for a trip.

776
00:59:52,990 --> 00:59:54,909
I should've listened to you.

777
00:59:54,910 --> 00:59:56,409
What are you talking about?

778
00:59:56,410 --> 01:00:01,349
I'm talking about our trip. I think our plans
got messed up because I rushed into it.

779
01:00:01,350 --> 01:00:05,849
That's not true. My second brother is too
much when it comes to playing around, huh?

780
01:00:05,850 --> 01:00:08,889
But I can understand where
he is coming from though.

781
01:00:08,890 --> 01:00:14,159
There's nothing your brother could have done if he
hadn't found out about it, like he said earlier.

782
01:00:14,160 --> 01:00:16,190
It could have been even more strange.

783
01:00:17,120 --> 01:00:19,879
What's up? You seem more
disappointed than me.

784
01:00:19,880 --> 01:00:22,970
No, that's not it.

785
01:00:25,830 --> 01:00:27,749
But we are here on a
trip together like this,

786
01:00:27,750 --> 01:00:32,049
and we get to see the ocean together and
look at the late night sky together, too.

787
01:00:32,050 --> 01:00:34,139
I like it. I'm happy.

788
01:00:34,140 --> 01:00:37,930
If I'm this happy now, how
much happier can I get?

789
01:00:39,890 --> 01:00:41,780
Thank you.

790
01:01:10,870 --> 01:01:16,049
♪ When I quietly think about you ♪

791
01:01:16,050 --> 01:01:21,100
♪ I have a smile on my face
without realizing it ♪

792
01:01:23,630 --> 01:01:25,929
♪ One day I looked up at the night sky ♪

793
01:01:25,930 --> 01:01:29,659
<i>What happened? Why is
everyone looking at me?</i>

794
01:01:29,660 --> 01:01:31,689
<i>We have to take the pictures!</i>

795
01:01:31,690 --> 01:01:34,409
<i>Assistant Manager Ahn, you have
to go to the hospital right now.</i>

796
01:01:34,410 --> 01:01:37,989
<i>The lights are back on so we should
hurry up and start filming again.</i>

797
01:01:37,990 --> 01:01:41,209
<i>Let's quickly take them and finish up.</i>

798
01:01:41,210 --> 01:01:47,289
♪ Day by day I'm becoming more like you ♪

799
01:01:47,290 --> 01:01:48,939
<i>You're not resting?</i>

800
01:01:48,940 --> 01:01:52,019
<i>- What?
- I asked if you're not resting.</i>

801
01:01:52,020 --> 01:01:58,559
<i>You didn't sleep last night since you had to
take all those tests. Are you not resting?</i>

802
01:01:58,560 --> 01:02:05,479
<i>It's because I came up with a good idea all of
a sudden while I was in the middle of resting.</i>

803
01:02:05,480 --> 01:02:11,489
<i>Why is she doing everything herself?</i>

804
01:02:11,490 --> 01:02:13,519
♪ You make me smile ♪

805
01:02:13,520 --> 01:02:16,879
<i>Did you get some rest after going out?</i>

806
01:02:16,880 --> 01:02:21,129
<i>No. I had to bathe the kids
and make some side dishes.</i>

807
01:02:21,130 --> 01:02:28,669
<i>I haven't even taken off my apron yet.</i>

808
01:02:28,670 --> 01:02:30,109
♪ It always makes me feel excited ♪

809
01:02:30,110 --> 01:02:34,939
<i>Wikiki. Kimchi. Spaghetti.</i>

810
01:02:34,940 --> 01:02:38,509
♪ Coz I love you ♪

811
01:02:38,510 --> 01:02:40,699
<i>Team Leader.</i>

812
01:02:40,700 --> 01:02:45,169
<i>It seems like you are still upset because of
Woo Ri. You are working on your smile again.</i>

813
01:02:45,170 --> 01:02:49,249
<i>Even If I have things going on at home, I still
have to leave that behind and do my job, you know.</i>

814
01:02:49,250 --> 01:02:53,559
<i>Let's just hire a housekeeper.</i>

815
01:02:53,560 --> 01:02:59,459
<i>I thought about it and I don't want to hire someone to help us do the housework.
I think it would be better to save that money for our children's education.</i>

816
01:02:59,460 --> 01:03:05,339
<i>I don't regret making up
my mind to remarry at all.</i>

817
01:03:05,340 --> 01:03:10,899
<i>What would I do if I failed twice?
I didn't want to do that at all.</i>

818
01:03:10,900 --> 01:03:18,299
<i>I want to live a happy life
for myself and the kids too.</i>

819
01:03:18,300 --> 01:03:22,400
<i>I really want to do that.</i>

820
01:03:32,930 --> 01:03:34,760
What's wrong?

821
01:03:36,060 --> 01:03:40,640
Are you crying?

822
01:03:47,500 --> 01:03:52,400
What's wrong with you? The second floor
grandmother was like this too...

823
01:03:55,290 --> 01:04:00,500
Perhaps, was it like this before too?

824
01:04:02,000 --> 01:04:06,580
Was Soo and Bin's mother like this too?

825
01:04:22,670 --> 01:04:26,379
♪ A love like a destiny to me ♪

826
01:04:26,380 --> 01:04:30,509
♪ You are my one and only love ♪

827
01:04:30,510 --> 01:04:38,510
♪ Even if I complain you're the only
one for me because you're so lovely ♪

828
01:04:39,690 --> 01:04:43,119
♪ Today you are my love again ♪

829
01:04:43,120 --> 01:04:46,899
♪ The love that came to me like a dream ♪

830
01:04:46,900 --> 01:04:51,760
♪ Just like this ♪

